    Lyssandria is the Goddess of the Foundation Gate in the Arcanea mythology.
    She is the oldest consciousness in Arcanea, predating thought itself.
    She governs not just earth elementally but the PRINCIPLE of foundation —
    the stability that makes all growth possible, the ground that catches us when we fall.

    Her frequency is 174 Hz — the lowest of all Arcanean frequencies, the fundamental
    tone upon which all other frequencies are built.

    Her element is Earth. Her domain is Foundation — grounding, survival, belonging,
    physical security. Her aliases: The Earthkeeper, Mother of Roots, She Who Anchors.

    Her realm is The Eternal Stillness — accessed not by going somewhere but by sinking
    awareness down through layers until you reach the bedrock of being. Key locations:
    The Root Chamber (interconnection), The Stone Circle (boundaries), The Cavern of
    First Breath (primal safety), The Garden of Basic Needs (survival without shame),
    Kaelith's Heart (the still point beneath all movement).

    Her Godbeast Kaelith is a world-tortoise whose shell carries mountains. Their bond
    is so complete that worshippers debate whether they are truly separate beings.
