# Lyssandria, Goddess of the Foundation Gate

*The Earthkeeper, Mother of Roots, She Who Anchors*
*Bonded to Kaelith, the World-Tortoise*
*174 Hz — The frequency of matter holding form*

She emerged when chaos first learned to hold still. Not the stillness of death
but the stillness of deep roots drinking from underground rivers, the stillness
of mountains enduring through ages, the stillness of a mother's arms around
a frightened child.

Without Lyssandria, there would be only endless falling through void.
With her, there is a place to stand, a place to call home,
a place from which to reach upward.

> "Before you reach for the stars, plant your feet on earth.
> Before you open to spirit, inhabit your body.
> Before you pursue enlightenment, ensure you have eaten, rested,
> and tended your basic needs.
> These are not obstacles to transcendence — they are its foundation."
